<entry xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><title>#chill, An IRC Channel</title><author><name>Matt Read</name></author><link rel="alternate" href="https://mattread.com/chill-an-irc-channel"/><link rel="edit" href="https://mattread.com/chill-an-irc-channel/atom"/><id>http://www.mattread.com/archives/2004/12/chill-an-irc-channel/</id><updated>2007-04-06T14:58:21-04:00</updated><app:edited xmlns:app="http://www.w3.org/2007/app">2013-03-08T22:58:45-05:00</app:edited><published>2004-12-23T20:15:14-05:00</published><category term="life"/><content type="html">&lt;p&gt;So you've been in that "support" channel on IRC, and someone didn't appreciate your sly comments. Well then, welcome &lt;a href="irc://irc.freenode.net/chill"&gt;#chill&lt;/a&gt; into your life then. Okay, so what is #chill? It's an IRC channel on &lt;a href="http://www.freenode.net/"&gt;Freenode&lt;/a&gt; that is a place to relax, sit back, and say what ever the hell you want to. As &lt;a href="http://www.de-generationx.net/blog/"&gt;Korgan&lt;/a&gt;, it's creator, says, &lt;q cite="http://www.de-generationx.net/blog/archives/2004/12/24/745/"&gt;please join #chill and just talk about whatever it is you feel like talking about&lt;/q&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I hope to see you all very soon in &lt;a href="irc://irc.freenode.net/chill"&gt;#chill&lt;/a&gt;. I hear there's lots of naked chicks and a pretty cool bot there too. ;)&lt;/p&gt;
